SIMPLE: flexuous
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Flexuous
<hw>Flex"u*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>flexuosus</ets>, fr. <ets>flexus</ets> a bending, turning.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Having turns, windings, or flexures.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>Having alternate curvatures in
opposite directions; bent in a zigzag manner.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Wavering; not steady; flickering.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Flexural</ent>⟦br⟧
